title: [96. Unique Binary Search Trees](https://leetcode.cn/problems/unique-binary-search-trees/)

| English | 简体中文 |
96. Unique Binary Search Trees Description Given an integer n, return the number of structurally unique BST's (binary search trees) which has exactly n nodes of unique values from 1 to n.
 
Example 1:
Input: n = 3 Output: 5 Example 2:
Input: n = 1 Output: 1  
Constraints:
1 <= n <= 19 Related Topics Tree Binary Search Tree Math Dynamic Programming Binary Tree Similar Questions Unique Binary Search Trees II
